line_2: Till some kind Star dear S—y mark'd out thee,

line_1: And find our Ruin in Security;
line_2: Thus lull'd into a Sleep, we dosing lie,
In vain he'll to the Horns of th' Altar fly,

line_1: There, lulled by careless soft security,
line_2: Wrapt in a cloud unseen by mortal eye,

line_1: While thou wert lulled in false security
line_2: Constrained we left thee to thy destiny.
